"David" == David Albertz <dalbertz@rmv.state.ma.us> writes:

David> I agree.  Blots are a Nomic Entity the way the rules define
David> Nomic Entities.

No, they're not.  Blots have been nothing more than a notational
convention since the adoption of Oerjan's Indulgences Proposal.  What
we call a Blot is merely a convenient name for a negative Indulgence,
just as a Mil was a convenient name for a collection of Marks.  All
P/C does is change the notational convention.

David> I hadn't thought of it before 8(, but I think it may be true,
David> if the proposal does not make any provision for Payment Orders
David> to be issued for existing Blots, then they won't be issued
David> after the proposal passes. 

The ultimate provision of the Proposal accounts for that, by mandating
the creation of Payment Orders for negative quantities of currency
held.  Since a Blot is a negative quantity of Currency, a Player with
a negative quantity of Indulgences (e.g. Blots) will end up with a
Payment Order for Indulgences (e.g. Blots). 

>> It makes little sense to think of a Blot, even in the new
>> framework, and the above notwithstanding, as _not_ being an Entity
>> existing solely by virtue of the Rules defining it to exist.

David> Agree (see above).

Disagree (see above).


