Now wait a minute - no one-liners, please. 1586 says that a NE is
"something that exists solely by virtue of the Rules". We are agreed
that a Blot exists solely by virtue of the Rules, right ? What we
disagree about is whether it is "something" at all, or whether there
are no such things as Blots, but rather a convention whereby ANY
language whatsoever in the Rules that assigns Blots to a Player
is to be taken as equivalent to "A Payment Order of N Indulgences
is to be submitted by the Player who detected the penalty with
the Bank as payee and the Player against whom the Penalty is
assessed as payor". This would have to hold whether the Rules in
question refer to "A Player gains N Blots", which your 1435/2 covers,
but also "A penalty of N Blots", which it does not, and any number
of other constructions referring to Blots.

Also your 1435/2 has a reference to "the Player responsible for
detecting the change in Blots". This would mean "the Player responsible
for detecting a change in the total amount of Indulgences named in
Payment Orders not disputed or vacated with a given Player as the
payor". There are no such Players; only Players responsible for
reporting Infractions.

That 1435/2 is - or will be - hey, did the Proposal pass or not, I'd
hate to have wasted so much energy if it in fact failed :) - seriously
broken is not the problem. The problem is that it is written, as are
the rest of the Rules, as if Blots were still Nomic Entities.

As for 1435/1, note that it says that Blots _are_ negative amounts
of Indulgences. Not that "'Blot' is short for '-1 Indulgences'".


