"Charles" == Charles E Carroll <ccarroll@dfw.net> writes:

>>  No, it means that, when a Rule says "Blot", it really means "a
>> Payment Order for one Indulgence."

Charles> I'm afraid I don't see the distinction between the two.
Charles> Could you elaborate?

I take the present definition of a Blot as "an amount of -1
Indulgences" as a legislative synonym.  This, thus definition, and the
one that replaces it in P/C, are what are known as "rules of
construction" and thus do not create any entities in and of
themselves; they merely provide a shorthand for referring to entities
already existing.  There are a few other examples of such rules of
construction scattered throughout the Rules; for example, Rule 1023,
or the last paragraph of Rule 478.

