Basically, my argument is that it makes no sense to regard the
references to 'Payment Orders', 'Transfer Orders' etc in the new
PC Rules as references to your newly minted Currencies. The new
PC Rules speak of the vacation, satisfaction, execution, and
cancellation of such orders. I can make no sense of what it might
mean to execute a unit of your newly minted Currency. This remains
true even in light of your interesting discoveries about Blots. To
the extent that we can make sense of 'executing a Blot', it is because
we have a Rule which defines a Blot to be a certain kind of Payment
Order. (The phrase still sounds awkward.) We have no Rules which
define your newly minted Currencies to be certain kinds of Payment
Order, however, and that seems to me to doom your scam.

